title: Unconditional Generation
description: Since [Redacted] is an auto-regressive model, it is also possible to generate music from scratch. Below are some examples.

title: Controlling Note Density
description: [Redacted] allows for the note density (i.e. the number of note onsets) to be specified for each track. Here we resample the Piano track several times with different levels of density.

title: Bar-Level Inpainting
description: Here we explore some of the possibilities that Bar-Level inpainting can offer. [Redacted] allows for a set of bars to be selected and resampled, affording the user a fine-degree of control.

examples.caption: We start with a piece from the dataset.

Now we replace the first and third bars on each track in 22c.

title: Bach
description: Here we experiment with Bach Chorales, exploring the interesting possibilities of iterative generation.
